---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, GAME } from '../consts';
import { crops, cropsByProfit } from '../data/crops';
import GuideImage from '../components/GuideImage.astro';

const faq = [
  { q: 'Do you farm at night in Moonlight Peaks?', a: 'Yes. You play a vampire, so growing and nurturing is done by moonlight — just be back in your coffin before sunrise. Night farming is a signature twist on the cozy farming loop.' },
  { q: 'What is a Draculamb?', a: 'A Draculamb is one of the magical livestock you can raise on your farm. You can also keep an adorable three-eyed Hellkitten as a pet.' },
  { q: 'What kind of crops can you grow?', a: 'As a vampire you grow cursed, enchanted crops and glowing flowers — early examples include blood grapes, cruelcumbers, pumpkins, and nightshade. The full crop list, prices, seasons, and growth times will be added at launch.' },
];

const jsonLd = [
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: faq.map((f) => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: f.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a } })) },
  { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Farming', item: new URL('/farming', SITE.url).href },
  ] },
];
---
<Base
  title="Moonlight Peaks Farming: How Night-Time Crops & Animals Actually Work"
  description="Confirmed Moonlight Peaks farming guide: why you farm at night instead of day, Blood Grapes, the Barn (4,000 gold from Ridge), and animals like Cheeken, Draculamb, and Cowcula — real launch data, not guesswork."
  path="/farming"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Farming' }]}
  showExport
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Entry · Farm</p>
      <h1>Moonlight Peaks <em>farming</em> & enchanted crops</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        Confirmed at launch: Blood Grapes (5-day grow), a Barn from Ridge (4,000 gold), and
        magical livestock — Cheeken, Piggoat, Draculamb, and Cowcula. Here's how moonlit farming,
        enchanted crops, and magical livestock actually work. Updated {SITE.updated}.
      </p>

      <GuideImage imageId="farm-02" priority />

      <h2>Farming by moonlight</h2>
      <p>
        As a creature of the night, you do your growing and nurturing after dark — just remember to
        be back in your coffin before the sun comes up. It's the familiar plant-tend-harvest rhythm
        of a cozy farming sim, flipped to the night.
      </p>

      <h2>Enchanted crops & glowing flowers</h2>
      <p>
        Paranormal farming techniques lead to interesting results: you grow enchanted, glowing crops
        and flowers rather than ordinary produce. As a vampire your sustenance is cursed food, so
        you'll grow and curse crops — early ones spotted include <strong>blood grapes</strong>,
        "cruelcumbers", pumpkins, and nightshade. The full crop list with prices, seasons, and
        growth times will be documented here at launch.
      </p>

      <h2>Magical livestock & pets</h2>
      <p>
        Your farm isn't just plants. You can raise magical livestock such as <strong>Draculambs</strong>,
        and keep an adorable three-eyed <strong>Hellkitten</strong> as a pet around the homestead.
      </p>

      <h2>Magic & tools</h2>
      <p>
        Farming and witchcraft go hand in hand — you can water crops with telekinetic watering cans
        and learn <a href="/magic">spells</a> (including a watering minigame) that speed up farmwork
        and gathering. As you progress, you obtain new tools and develop your property to grow even more.
      </p>

      <h2>Crop database</h2>
      {crops.length > 0 ? (
        <table class="facts compact">
          <tr><th>Crop</th><th>Season</th><th>Buy</th><th>Sell</th><th>Grow days</th><th>Regrow</th><th>Status</th></tr>
          {crops.map((c) => (
            <tr>
              <td>{c.name}</td>
              <td>{c.season.length ? c.season.join(', ') : '—'}</td>
              <td>{c.buyPrice ?? '—'}</td>
              <td>{c.sellPrice ?? '—'}</td>
              <td>{c.growDays ?? '—'}</td>
              <td>{c.regrowDays ?? '—'}</td>
              <td>{c.status}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </table>
      ) : (
        <p>Crop data will be added as it is verified in the live game.</p>
      )}

      {cropsByProfit.length > 0 && (
        <>
          <h2>Best crops for money</h2>
          <ol>{cropsByProfit.map((c) => (<li>{c.name} — {c.sellPrice}g</li>))}</ol>
        </>
      )}

      <h2>Livestock — confirmed buying flow</h2>
      <p>
        Confirmed at launch: you can't buy animals right away. First buy a <strong>Barn</strong> from
        <a href="/characters/ridge">Ridge</a> for <strong>4,000 gold plus materials</strong>
        (10x6 space, takes 1 night to build, holds 4 animals), then buy
        livestock from <a href="/characters/luna">Luna</a> — only the animals currently waiting
        outside her house. Confirmed animal types: <strong>Cheeken</strong> (a common first buy, which
        likes being petted and bought hats), <strong>Piggoat</strong>, <strong>Draculamb</strong>, and
        <strong>Cowcula</strong>. Feed them with Fodder (made via a refiner), or the better Premium
        Fodder once you unlock it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Confirmed tool note: your Pickaxe is the top upgrade priority — breaking bigger rocks in your
        home area frees up space for extra barns and other buildings.
      </p>
      <p>
        Confirmed farm add-ons: a <strong>Scarecrow</strong> protects crops from ravens in a set
        radius around it, and a <strong>Beehive</strong> (an early Luna blueprint) covers an area
        shown when placing it. Processing machines confirmed so far: the <strong>Keg</strong> (wine,
        beer, juices), the <strong>Refiner</strong> (planks from wood, refined stone from rocks,
        fiber into Fodder — its blueprint unlocks after fixing your house's roof), and the
        <strong>Furnace</strong> (charcoal from wood, ores into bars or glass).
      </p>

      <h2>Vampster side-quest</h2>
      <p>
        Confirmed at launch: small black Vampster creatures hide around your land. You can only carry
        one at a time while in your bat/vampire form (they don't go in your inventory), and the quest
        is to bring each one you find to a cave near Orlock's mansion.
      </p>

      <h2>Still being verified</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Livestock care</strong> and what each animal produces.</li>
        <li>Farm spots marked on the <a href="/map">interactive map</a>.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        {faq.map((f) => (
          <details>
            <summary>{f.q}</summary>
            <p>{f.a}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="callout wip">
        Pre-launch entry — crop and livestock data lands at launch. Related:
        <a href="/magic">magic</a>, <a href="/items">items</a>, <a href="/environment">environment</a>, <a href="/map">interactive map</a>, <a href="/beginner-guide">beginner guide</a>.
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
